access modifier controlls visibilties, not behaviour


private - same class   // you cannot make a class as private 9 only variable and methods ( but inner class can be private) 
  public - everywhere
  protected - package & subclass  // you cannot make class as protected only fields and method
  default - same package
------- ------- ------ ------  ------  ------  

A. private access modifier exqmple 

you cannot make a class as private  only variable and methods 
üí°( but inner class can be private) 
why bcz it should be accessible to the JVM and other classes in the packages!

class Employee
  private int sal;
  private void showSal() {}

void test(){
  showSalary() //allowded

//not accessible outside the classs
Employee e = new Employee();
e.salary //compilation error

Project use case:
Utility/helper methods inside a service are often private to prevent misuse and unintended overrides
