C. protected - package + child
------------------------------

protected member be accessed outside pacakage
‚úÖ Yes ‚Äî but only through inheritance
‚ùå Not allowed via object reference:


package com.company.a

public class Parent {
  protected int bounus = 20000;

same packge//
Parent p = new Parent();
p.bounus() // allowed

different package//

package com.company.b
import com.company.a

class child extends Parent {
void show() {
  //allowded
}

but different package + not child

Parent p = new Parent();
p.bonus() //not allowded

